class="comment-meta">Posted April 20, 2010 at 11:39 pm <span
class="meta-sep">|</span> <a
href="#comment-28120" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a></div><div
class="comment-content"><p>I&#8217;ve been hunting all over to get a sub made in my area with this kind of bread.  There are even some sub shops that have it shipped from Amoroso’s. Weird thing is, by the time it gets here, the roll turns into a large hot dog bun!<br
/> After much frustration I decided to simply break down and make it myself.  Great recipe and very simple, not even much mixing is required.</p><p>Used an air-bake cookie sheet on which I wiped with Crisco and dusted with cornmeal and then allowed the rolls to rise on the sheet. Put an empty metal bread pan on the floor of the gas oven and added 1/2C of water after the bread was in place on the rack. Instant steam that way but not sure if it matters.  Got 4 standard sub rolls out of this recipe and they came out really well. Check my web link to see  the beauties.</p></div><div
