class="fn n"><a
href='http://cooklikeyourgrandmother.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url url'>Drew</a></span></div><div
class="comment-meta">Posted July 29, 2010 at 3:28 pm <span
class="meta-sep">|</span> <a
href="#comment-29427" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a></div><div
class="comment-content"><p>Diedre, that sounds horrible. So sorry it&#8217;s not working.</p><p>My best guess for the temperature is that you&#8217;re trying to proof in a metal bowl. The metal acts as a heat sink &#8212; like the fins in a car radiator &#8212; and draw the heat out.</p><p>If you want to proof in the same metal bowl you&#8217;re going to mix in, rinse the bowl in hot water first so it doesn&#8217;t draw all the heat out of the water.</p></div><div
class="comment-reply-link"><a
rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2008/12/how-to-make-crusty-italian-bread/?replytocom=29427#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-29427", "29427", "respond", "1735")'>Reply</a></div><ul
